WLR Tutorial

  1. We load the CITE-seq human PBMC data. You can follow the Seurat tutorial or download the analyzed R object.
cbmc <- readRDS(file = "cbmc.data.rds")

cannot open compressed file 'cbmc.data.rds', probable reason 'No such file or directory'Error in gzfile(file, "rb") : cannot open the connection
  1. We run WLR on the RNA data.
print(x = ptm1 - ptm)

   user  system elapsed 
 45.262  13.995  76.852
  1. We run WLR on the ADT data.
print(x = ptm1 - ptm)

   user  system elapsed 
 33.684  11.248  57.830
  1. We fuse the RNA and ADT data. We see that CD4+ and CD8+ T cells are more defined by the ADT data in the surface protein space, while Dendritic cells (pDCs) are more defined in the RNA-seq data due to the absence of its surface marker in the ADT data.

  1. We perform UMAP dimensional reduction on the fused data. Additionally, clustering can be performed as well.
